  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">For a symmetric pair <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>G</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>H</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> of reductive groups we construct a family of intertwining operators between spherical principal series representations of G and H that are induced from parabolic subgroups satisfying certain compatibility conditions. The operators are given explicitly in terms of their integral kernels and we prove convergence of the integrals for an open set of parameters and meromorphic continuation. In particular, this establishes lower bounds for multiplicities of intertwining operators.</subfield>
